@startuml User Authentication Flow
title User Authentication Flow - Sequence Diagram

actor User
participant "Client App" as Client
participant "Auth Service" as Auth
participant "JWT Manager" as JWT
participant "User DB" as DB

User -> Client: Enter Username & Password
activate Client

Client -> Auth: POST /auth/login\n(username, password)
activate Auth

Auth -> DB: Query User by Username
activate DB
DB --> Auth: User Record (with hashed pwd)
deactivate DB

Auth -> Auth: Compare Password Hash\nvs Input Password
alt Password Match
    Auth -> JWT: Generate JWT Token
    activate JWT
    JWT -> JWT: Create JWT\n(userId, role, exp: 24h)
    JWT --> Auth: Signed Token
    deactivate JWT
    
    Auth --> Client: 200 OK\n{\n  "accessToken": "eyJ...",\n  "user": {"id": "123", "role": "user"}\n}
else Password Mismatch
    Auth --> Client: 401 Unauthorized\n{"error": "Invalid credentials"}
end

deactivate Auth

Client -> Client: Store access token\n(localStorage/sessionStorage)
Client --> User: Login Success
deactivate Client

@enduml
